		(company "Gonoboben/plataVM")
		(comment 1 "V1.6 PCB-C boundary: local control/ADC, CAN-FD data and direct SAFE/HARD_OFF")
		(comment 2 "Detailed hierarchy 31..36; no components, connectors or footprints selected")
	)
	(lib_symbols)
	(text "30_POWER_12V_TOP - V1.6 HIERARCHY MAP\nPCB-C receives PACK_BUS_P12_IN and distributes fourteen protected 12 V outputs.\nCH1..CH11 are normally commanded; CH12..CH14 are Always-On monitored in RUN.\nEach channel is 3 A continuous / 5 A peak up to 1 s, subject to total 30 A hardware rating and system power budget."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 12 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.30 1.30)) (justify left))
		(uuid "p12-v16-30-101")
	)
	(text "LOCAL CONTROL / TRANSPORT\nPCB-C contains local protected I/O/ADC and a CAN-FD node. Normal channel enables, current/fault/status, input voltage and board temperature are CAN-FD data objects.\nP12_GROUP_SAFE_OFF and P12_GROUP_HARD_OFF are direct hardware inputs; P12_BOARD_FAULT_N is a direct summary output."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 84 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.10 1.10)) (justify left))
		(uuid "p12-v16-30-102")
	)
	(text "SUB-SHEETS 31..36\n31 input protection; 32 channel template; 33 CH1..CH7; 34 CH8..CH14; 35 local diagnostics/data aggregation; 36 power/output/CAN/hard-line connector boundary.\nNo channel current passes through PCB-B."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 150 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.08 1.08)) (justify left))
		(uuid "p12-v16-30-103")
	)
	(text "FAIL-SAFE RULES\nLocal overcurrent/thermal protection remains active without CAN-FD. Communication loss blocks new normal commands and reports a fault when communication is available again.\nSAFE/HARD_OFF override normal setpoints. CH12..CH14 are not exempt from protection or hardware OFF."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 212 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.08 1.08)) (justify left))
		(uuid "p12-v16-30-104")
	)
